oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Ray Price recording session outtakes - April's Fool -1969-09-03
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Copy of a 4 track tape of the Ray Price Columbia Records recording session for the song April's Fool. Produced by Don Law and recorded at Columbia Studio A in Nashville. Transferred from analog tape to rewritable MiniDisc by unidentified source and given to CMF. Includes session banter, false starts, breakdowns, etc.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Ray Price; Grady Martin;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: (00:00) Take one of April's Fool begins in progress / (01:02) Intermittent breaks in program due to MD playback failure / (01:32) Take one continues / (02:51) Take two / (05:19) Take three / (06:05) Take four / (08:46) Ray asked Grady Martin what he's doing wrong / (09:20) Take five / (12:15) Take six / (15:12) Take seven / (17:25) abrupt ending / (17:57) FILE END
